It sounds like you&#39;ll want to define a ContentNegotiationCongiurer. Here&#39;s a doc: https://www.baeldung.com/spring-mvc-content-negotiation-json-xml

The short answer is to add something like this to the Spring context

```
@Configuration
public class WebConfig extends WebMvcConfigurerAdapter {
    @Override
    public void configureContentNegotiation(ContentNegotiationConfigurer configurer) {
        configurer.defaultContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);
    }
}
```

You can force a JSON response with the following configuration:

    @Configuration
    public class WebConfig implements WebMvcConfigurer {

        @Override
        public void configureContentNegotiation(ContentNegotiationConfigurer configurer) {
            configurer.strategies(List.of(new FixedContentNegotiationStrategy(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)));
        }
    }

